METS_Profile.title: METS profile for all different IP in Sweden.
METS_Profile.abstract: This is the basic profile for digital IP's in Sweden created by the project eARD. It can be used as a base for SIP, AIP and DIP's. In this profile all datafiles must be referenced in the IP. Curator of the basic profile is to be decided. The profile is developed by Riksarkivet (RA), the National Archives of Sweden in the projekt eARD. The profile is based on the work made by ENSAM and the profiles called SWEIP and SWEIPB. The this profile is supersiding these two.

contact.name: Karin Bredenberg
contact.institution: Riksarkivet, The National Archives of Sweden

METS_Profile.related_profile: No related profiles for this profile. This is a base profile that should be extended, and used in conjunction with a delivery specific specification

resource_model.p: This profile is intended to work in all different kind of solutions and stages of the OAIS-model as a base profile

note.p: No external schemas used in this profile.

description_rules.p: It's recommended that context data confirms to all suitable standards. If the reciver of the IP have recommendations these also needs to be followed

description.head: mets/@TYPE
description.p: These are the originally supported values for the TYPE attribut in METS for objects confirming to this profile.
SIP - Submission Information Package - Inkommande paket - det paket som lämnas till det digitala arkivet
AIP - Archival Information Package - Arkivpaket - det paket som lagras
DIP - Dissemination Information Package - Utlämningspaket - det paket som lämnas ut
AIC - Archival Information Collection - Arkivpaket samling - en samlingspost för flera arkivpaket
AIU - Archival Information Unit - Arkivinformations enhet - det minsta objektet som kan lagras i det digitala arkivet, kan bestå av flera filer

description.head: mets/amdSec/***MD/@OTHERMDTYPE
description.p: These are the originally supported values for the OTHERMDTYPE attribut in METS for objects confirming to this profile.
ADDML - a standard for describing databases
EAC-F - a comming standard for describing functions
EAG - a standard for describing the archival institution
METS
COMMENT - a way to insert a comment regarding the delivery

description.head: mets/metsHdr/Agent/@OTHERTYPE
description.p: These are the originally supported values for the OTHERTYPE attribut in METS for objects confirming to this profile.
SOFTWARE - a program that has been involved in the process of the IP

description.head: mets/metsHdr/@RECORDSTATUS
description.p: SUPPLEMENT - extends the previous delivery
REPLEACEMENT - replaces the previous delivery
NEW - a new delivery
TEST - a test delivery
VERSION - a delivery with same content regarding files but one or more files have a new version
OTHER - status not in list
To be decided - more values to come

vocabulary.name: Vocabulary for attribute TYPE in altRecordID

description.head: mets/metsHDR/altRecordID/@TYPE
description.p: DELIVERYTYPE - Which deliverytype does the package belong to
DELIVERYSPECIFICATION - Deliveryspecification for delivery type
SUBMISSIONAGREEMENT - Identification and date for delivery agreement
PREVIOUSSUBMISSIONAGREEMENT - Identification and date for previous submission agreement seperated with a ;
DATASUBMISSIONSESSION - Session in delivery agreement
PACKAGENUMBER - A serial number for the package in a session
REFERENCECODE - Referencecode in archival description
PREVIOUSREFERENCECODE - Earlier reference code in archival description
APPRAISAL - States if the packages contains files that can be appraised or not. Which files is shown in for example the archival description or in the delivery specific information.
ACCESSRESTRICT - States if the package contains files that have access restrict of any kind. Which files is shown in for example the archival description or in the delivery specific information.
STARTDATE - Startingdate for delivered information
ENDDATE - Ending date for delivered information
INFORMATIONCLASS - The deliverers own specification of the highest informationclass information availiable in the package
SYSTEMTYPE - The origination systemtype for the package

vocabulary.name: Vocabulary for deliverytype and systemtype specification

description.head: mets/metsHDR/altRecordID/@TYPE="DELIVERYSPECIFICATION"
description.p: ERMS - Electronic Record Management System - Ärende och dokumenthantering
Personnel - Personnel systems - Personal
Journals - Journals from for example health care - Journal
Economics - Economics systems - Ekonomi
Databases - Databases in flatfiles - Register/Databaser
Webpages - Webpages and whole sites - Webbplatser
GIS - Geografical Information Systems - Geografiska informationssystem
No specification - No assigned specification exist - Ingen specifikation finns
AIC - A collection of packages (AIC) - Samlingspaket
Publication - An electronical publication - Publikation
Deposit - Material delivered to a library according to for example the law about e-plikt - Deposition
Agreement - Material delivered to a library with a special agreement for exampel when e-plikt isn't the case - Överenskommen leverans
Noark 3- Delivery of the type Noark 3 - Noark 3 leverans
Noark 4- Delivery of the type Noark 4 - Noark 4 leverans
Noark 5- Delivery of the type Noark 5 - Noark 5 leverans
Fagsystem - A registration system with sometimes different kind of information - Registreringssystem

description.head: mets/metsHDR/agent/@OTHERROLE
description.p: PRODUCER - Describes the unit or organisation resposible for creation of the METS-document - Skaparen av paketet
SUBMITTER - Describes the unit or organisation resposible for delivery of the METS-document - Den specifika leverantören
These are the originally supported namespaces for objects confirming to this profile.

vocabulary.name: Vocabulary for use when altRecordID type APPRAISAL is used

description.p: These are the values to show if the package contains material that can be appraised or not. Which files are shown in the specific XML-file describing the delivery according to deliveryspecification
Yes - The package contains material that can be appraised
No - The package contains nothing to appraise

vocabulary.name: Vocabulary for use when altRecordID type ACCESSRESTRICT is used

description.p: These are the values to show if the package contains material that have accessrestrictions. Which files are shown in the specific XML-file describing the delivery according to deliveryspecification
Secrecy - The package contains files with confidentiality
PUL - The package contains files with confidentiality regarding personal statesment
Secrecy and PUL - The package cointains both confidentiality and personal confidentiality

vocabulary.name: Vocabulary for use when agent has an identification code

description.p: These are the values to use when the agent has an identification code
VAT - The VAT-number is used - Momsnummer används
DUNS - The DUNS-number is used - DUNS-nummer används
ORG - The swedish organication number is used - Organisationsnummer används
HSA - An HSA-ID is used - HSA id används
Local - An own defined code is used - En egen kod används
URI - An URN or URL as identification - En URI används

vocabulary.name: Vocabulary for use when formatkey is used

description.p: These are the values to use when an formatkey from an formatregistry is usedthe agent has an identification code
PRONOM - The PRONOM registry is used

description.head: METS root-element
Namespaces
description.p: All elements are referenced with a namespace-prefix.

description.head: XSI
description.p: Xsi-definititions are made according to vcNAMESPACES

description.head: Schemalocations
description.p: The following schema locations are used to make xml-files following this profile able to validate
xsi:schemaLocation="http://http://www.loc.gov/METS/ http://????????/eARD_Paket_FGS_mets.xsd"

description.head: Attributes
description.p: The attributes PROFILE, OBJID and TYPE values must be set
PROFILE is set to the profile that has been used to create the document.
OBJID is set with an globally unique identifier like an GUID or an UUID. The value must be precideed with the name of the type like GUID: and then followed by the value
TYPE is set according to vocabulary vcMETS_TYPE. Example: SIP
The attribute LABEL is recommended for use
LABEL is set to a descriptive title. Example: Intern bildbatch lagring
The attribute ID can be used, it's the identification when referencing itself in the METs-document
ID is set with for example UUID or GUID and starts with an added "ID"

description.head: METS-document filename
description.p: The name can't have swedish characters, space or special characters.
These characters are allowed: a..z, A..Z, 1..9, "-" and "_"

description.head: metsHdr-element
description.p: The CREATEDATE attribute must be set.
CREATEDATE is set to the creation date of the package in the form yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ss+01:00

description.head: metsHdr-element
description.p: The RECORDSTATUS attribute can be set to indicate the status of the package
RECORDSTATUS uses a vocabulary

description.head: Agent-element
description.p: The metsHdr-element must contain at least three agent-element.

description.head: Agent-element-attributes
description.p: The attribute ID is not used
The attribute ROLE is used
The attribute OTHERROLE is used when ROLE has value OTHER
The attribute TYPE is used
The attribute OTHERTYPE is used when TYPE has value OTHER

description.head: Agent-element-name-element
description.p: The name of the agent
Example: "Karin Bredenberg".
Example: "Myndigheten"

description.head: Agent-element-note-element
description.p: Information about the agent and the identification code
Can be zero ore more note-elements.
Usually one note element will be present

description.head: First mandatory agent
description.p: ROLE="ARCHIVIST" TYPE="ORGANIZATION"
Describes the archival creator
An note element will be used to state the identification number
The identification number will be type identified with a prefix from vcTypeOfIdentificationCode followed by a ":"

description.head: Second mandatory agent
description.p: ROLE="CREATOR" TYPE="ORGANIZATION"
Describes the unit or organisation resposible for creation and delivery of the METS-document
An note element will be used to state the identification number
The identification number will be type identified with a prefix from vcTypeOfIdentificationCode followed by a ":"

description.head: Third mandatory agent
description.p: ROLE="ARCHIVIST" TYPE="OTHER" OTHERTYPE="SOFTWARE"
Describes the creation software for the material delivered
If no common name for the software use a describing text
Use note element to state the version

description.head: Suggestion of complementary agents
description.p: We suggest the use of some complementary agents. For details look in the example

description.head: First complementary agent
description.p: ROLE="EDITOR" TYPE="ORGANIZATION"
Describes the unit or organisation who has aided in the creation and delivery of the METS-document
An note element will be used to state the identification number
The identification number will be type identified with a prefix from vcTypeOfIdentificationCode followed by a ":"

description.head: Second complementary agent
description.p: ROLE="CREATOR" TYPE="OTHER" OTHERTYPE="SOFTWARE"
Describes the creation software for package
If no common name for the software use a describing text
Use note element to state the version

description.head: Third complementary agent
description.p: ROLE="PRESERVATION" TYPE="ORGANIZATION"
Describes the unit or organisation who administrates the e-archive
An note element will be used to state the identification number
The identification number will be type identified with a prefix from vcTypeOfIdentificationCode followed by a ":"

description.head: Fourth complementary agent
Can occur several times
description.p: ROLE="CREATOR" TYPE="INDIVIDUAL"
Describes the person who can be contacted regarding the delivery in the delivery moment.
Use note to state contacts phone number and e-mail
This information is only valid for a short period

description.head: Fifth complementary agent
description.p: ROLE="IPOWNER" TYPE="ORGANIZATION"
Describes the Information owner
An note element will be used to state the identification number
The identification number will be type identified with a prefix from vcTypeOfIdentificationCode followed by a ":"

description.head: Sixth complementary agent
description.p: ROLE="OTHER" OTHERROLE="PRODUCER" TYPE="ORGANIZATION"
Describes the unit or organisation resposible for creation of the METS-document (Deliverer)
Used to give a more detailed description of the creation progress in combination with second mandatory agent
An note element will be used to state the identification number
The identification number will be type identified with a prefix from vcTypeOfIdentificationCode followed by a ":"

description.head: Seventh complementary agent
description.p: ROLE="OTHER" OTHERROLE="SUBMITTER" TYPE="ORGANIZATION"
Describes the unit or organisation resposible for delivery of the METS-document
Used to give a more detailed description of the creation progress in combination with second mandatory agent
An note element will be used to state the identification number
The identification number will be type identified with a prefix from vcTypeOfIdentificationCode followed by a ":"

description.head: metsDocumentID-element
description.p: The metsHdr-element should contain the metsDocumentID-element
Is set according to rules in extending profiles. The recommendetion is to use the METS-file name.

description.head: altRecordID-element
description.p: The metsHdr-element must contain at least three altRecordID-element.

description.head: First mandatory altRecordID
description.p: TYPE="DELIVERYTYPE"
Describes the delivery type the package belongs to

description.head: Second mandatory altRecordID

description.head: Third mandatory altRecordID

description.head: Second complementary altRecordID

description.head: Third complementary altRecordID

description.head: Fourth complementary altRecordID

description.head: Fifth complementary altRecordID

description.head: Seventh complementary altRecordID

description.head: Eight complementary altRecordID

Startingdate for delivered information

description.head: Ninth complementary altRecordID

description.head: Tenth complementary altRecordID
description.p: TYPE="INFORMATIONCLASS"

description.head: Eleventh complementary altRecordID
description.p: TYPE="SYSTEMTYPE"
The originationg systemtype for the information in the package

description.p: xmlData or binData is used

description.head: When mdWrap is used these rules apply
description.p: When embedding is used, a namespaces prefix is used.
The mdWrap-element attributes used: MDTYPE= According to METS-schema OTHERMDTYPE= According to vcOTHERMDTYPE

description.head: mdRef
description.p: An mdRef element referencing metadata in a file in the case of the file being to large to embedd

description.head: When mdRef is used and points to a referenced file inside the package these rules apply
description.p: The mdRef-element attributes used: The attribute ID contains the unique identifier (for example UUID or GUID) and starts with an added "ID" for the element in the METS-document MIMETYPE according to the referenced files mimetype LOCTYPE="URL" MDTYPE according to METS-schema OTHERMDTYPE= According to vcOTHERMDTYPE MDTYPEVERSION records filformat and version for the file in the form "format name";"version";"format registry";"formatkey" SIZE according to the referenced filesize in bytes CREATED according to the date of the referenced file in the format yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ss+01:00 CHECKSUMTYPE according to METS-schema (Not mandatory) CHECKSUM the calculated checksum value (Not mandatory) xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="file:nameOfFile.xml" this is the name of the file and it has prefix file:

description.head: When mdRef is used and it points to a resource like LIBRIS these rules apply
description.p: In case of a persistent link referenced in the IP the mdRef-element attributes used:

The mdRef-element attributes used: The attribute ID contains the unique identifier for the element in the METS-document LOCTYPE="URL" MDTYPE according to METS-schema OTHERMDTYPE= According to vcOTHERMDTYP xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="http://nameOfReference.html" this is the referenced link
Zero or more amdSec is present

The attribute ID's value starts with ID

description.p: When embedding is used, a namespaces prefix is used.
The mdWrap-element attributes used: MDTYPE= According to METS-schema OTHERMDTYPE= According to vcOTHERMDTYPE
xmlData or binData is used

description.head: mdRef

The mdRef-element attributes used: The attribute ID contains the unique identifier (for example UUID or GUID) and starts with an added "ID" for the element in the METS-document MIMETYPE according to the referenced files mimetype LOCTYPE="URL" MDTYPE according to METS-schema OTHERMDTYPE= According to vcOTHERMDTYPE MDTYPEVERSION records filformat and version for the file in the form "format name";"version";"format registry";"formatkey" SIZE according to the referenced filesize in bytes CREATED according to the date of the referenced file in the format yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ss+01:00 CHECKSUMTYPE according to METS-schema (Not mandatory) CHECKSUM the calculated checksum value (Not mandatory) xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="file:nameOfFile.xml"

description.head: Comment
techMD
description.p: To be able to insert a comment one techMD is used
One techMD is present
The attribute ID contains the unique identifier (for example UUID or GUID) and starts with an added "ID" for the element in the METS-document
The attribute ID's value starts with "ID"
mdWrap is used
One xmlData is present
In the xmlData an element namned comment is present. In this element the comment is written
The element comment uses the prefix "comment" and the namespace xmlns:comment="commentnamespace"

description.head: digiprovMD
description.p: Zero or more digiprovMD is present

The attriubte ID's value starts with "ID"
The recommendation is to use PREMIS for this type of information
mdWrap or mdRef is used

description.head: sourceMD
description.p: No sourceMD is required
The attribute ID contains the unique identifier (for example UUID or GUID) and starts with an added "ID" for the element in the METS-document
The attribute ID's value starts with "ID"
mdWrap or mdRef is used
One fileSec element is present
There are one or more fileGrp elements.

description.head: fileGrp
description.p: The attribute USE is strongly recommended

description.head: file element
description.p: Each file element should have this attributes set (mandatory): ID contains the unique identifier (for example UUID or GUID) and starts with an added "ID" for the element in the METS-document MIMETYPE according to the referenced files mimetype LOCTYPE according to METS-schema xlink:href records the filename SIZE according to the referenced filesize in bytes CREATED according to the date of the referenced file in the format yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:ss+01:00 USE records filformat and version for the file in the form "format name";"version" after that ;"format registry"(according to vcTypeOfFormatregistry):"formatkey"

Recommended attributes for the file element not mandatory: CHECKSUMTYPE according to METS-schema (This is a change from the origination work made by ENSAM) CHECKSUM the calculated checksum value (This is a change from the origination work made by ENSAM) GROUPID to identify files with special function ADMID can referens to the technical metadata id (example: ID550e8400-e29b-41d4-a716-4466554400xx) referencing the correct technical metadata section DMDID can referens to the descreptive metadata id (example: ID550e8400-e29b-41d4-a716-4466554400aa) referencing the correct descriptive metadata section
Each file element will have a FLocat-element pointing to the referenced file
Each FLocat element will have these attributes set: LOCTYPE according to METS-schema xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="file:nameOfFile.xml"
Every xlink:href will have the prefix "file:" before the filename.

description.head: transformFile
description.p: transformFile can be used to give encryptionkey and algorithm for encrypted files
Elements and attriubtes mandatory when using transformFile is used.
Attributes TRANSFORMTYPE, TRANSFORMKEY, TRANSFORMALGORITHM and TRANSFORMORDER are used
One or more structmap-elements is present
When there are more than one structmap use of the attribute LABEL is recommended for describing what the structmap is presenting
The structmap are built up with div's according to extending profile.

description.head: Div
description.p: Can contain one or more div-elements
Contains zero or more pointers to files, fptr
div/fptr/FILEID points to one file in the filesec

description.head: div-element attributes
description.p: Recommended attributes for the div element not mandatory: LABEL according to extending profiles vocabulary ADMID referencing zero or more ADMID's used for files referenced through fptr-elements DMDID referencing zero or more DMDMID's used for files referenced through fptr-elements
No structLink is required
No behaviorSec is required
No multiSection is required
Requirements which span METS documents sections should appear in the multiSection subelement
All content files should follow known specifications.

description.head: XML Schemas
description.p: All xml-files should have their schemas with them as a part of the package, to allow validation aganist the correct schema.
The schemas should in the structmap be grouped thogether and have a label that indicates that it's a group of schemas
No behavior requirements requiered
None
